"""GaussianNonCentralChiSquaredPolynomial — orthogonal polynomial for quadrature.

# C++ parity: ql/experimental/math/gaussiannoncentralchisquaredpolynomial.{hpp,cpp}
# @ v1.42.1 (099987f0).

Builds the orthogonal polynomial of the non-central chi-squared distribution
(parameters ``nu`` degrees of freedom, ``lambda`` non-centrality) for use with
a moment-based Gaussian quadrature. The recurrence coefficients ``alpha`` /
``beta`` are derived from the distribution moments via the Golub-Welsch /
Morandi-Cecchi modified-moment algorithm encoded in
:class:`MomentBasedGaussianPolynomial`.

The first ``_MOMENTS`` (28) non-central chi-squared moments are pre-computed as
closed-form polynomials in ``(nu, lambda)`` — a direct port of the
``boost::preprocessor``-generated moment table ``f_0 .. f_27`` in the C++ source.
The weight ``w(x)`` is the non-central chi-squared pdf, evaluated here via
:func:`scipy.stats.ncx2`.

# C++ parity divergence: the C++ ``MomentBasedGaussianPolynomial`` is a class
# template ``<mp_real>`` that can run the recurrence in arbitrary precision
# (boost.multiprecision) to fight cancellation. The Python port runs the
# recurrence in double precision only (``mp_real == float``); this matches the
# C++ ``Real`` specialization and is sufficient for the quadrature-node-sum
# cross-check at the C++ 1e-5 test tolerance. Arbitrary-precision moment
# accumulation is documented as a carve-out (would require ``mpmath``).
"""

